Now I'm going to turn the presentation over to Casey Perkins who will talk a bit about the OR team projects that helped define our teams' impact.

What we wanted from the team:
	- Mainly this was a sense of belonging and inspiration
	- Wanted to Collaborate
	- Ability to learn new things



	I won't go into much detail here for the sake of time but I'd be happy to answer questions off line or one on one with anyone who is interested.

	as you can see, there are a number of people with R in Group C.
	- From this we can take a few paths
		1) That person shouldn't use R any more
		2) That person want's to improve their R skills so they should collaborate with someone who already has a competitive advantage so they can most rapidly get into Group A.

		From this exercise, we were able to visualize how we can better collaborate as a group and where our team can have the best chances for success.